Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Engineer position with ResMed. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack web applications, RESTful APIs, and cloud-native systems, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I developed and consumed RESTful APIs across 1,000+ platform endpoints using client-server architecture, translating natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls within an n-tier enterprise application architecture — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and safe execution across a distributed microservices surface. I built API-aware templates, SDK patterns, and code-generation workflows to accelerate full-stack developer integration with platform REST APIs, improving implementation correctness. To keep these systems production-ready, I implemented an observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks to troubleshoot production issues and track quality, reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and API costs by 50% through targeted concurrency and routing optimizations. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to the backbone infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis handling file operations in Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs — giving me direct, hands-on experience with cloud-native, multi-environment backend design. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with Object-Oriented Programming principles, and developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to handle long-running data import jobs and prevent AWS Lambda timeouts, troubleshooting production systems — both of which required the kind of systems-level thinking and operational stability focus this role demands. I participated in code reviews and collaborated with cross-functional teams (QA, product, design) in an Agile/Scrum environment using Git for version control throughout the software development lifecycle. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to building and maintaining software features, developing and consuming RESTful APIs, and working with databases to query and update data.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, GPU-accelerated computing, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster for model training and fine-tuning. I was responsible for managing the full model development lifecycle — from data preparation and training runs to inference optimization using vLLM and deployment via Hugging Face — ensuring both performance and secure, efficient model serving. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents for an audience of 50+ students, demonstrating strong communication and collaboration skills. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the ability to write clean, maintainable, and well-documented code with guidance and work effectively within a team environment. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to this team and its mission.

I have always been passionate about improving health and quality of life through innovative technology and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of ResMed's mission to help people sleep, breathe and live better, empowering 500 million lives by 2030 through home-based care. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

